# Accessibility (Visionary)

Source of truth: `docs/design.md` — Accessibility Standards and Motion (Reduced Motion).

Target: **WCAG 2.1 Level AA** minimum for all Visionary products.

## Contrast

Before shipping new token pairings, verify ratios from the spec:

- Body text on background: **4.5:1**
- Large text (18px+ regular, 14px+ bold): **3:1**
- UI components / graphical objects: **3:1**
- Focus indicator vs adjacent colors: **3:1**
- Text on solid action or status fills: **4.5:1** (use `text.on-solid` or `status.*.on-solid`)

## Focus

Every interactive element needs a visible keyboard focus state:

- Use `:focus-visible`, not `:focus` alone
- Ring: **2px solid** `focus.ring`, **2px offset**, offset color `focus.ring-offset`, radius inherits
- Do not remove outlines without this compliant replacement
- Do not invent per-component focus colors
- Nested interactives each get their own focus ring

## Touch Targets

- Minimum hit area: **44px** (`touch-target.minimum`)
- Prefer **48px** on mobile where space allows
- Gap between targets: `spacing.2`
- Icon-only controls: expand hit area to 44px minimum

## Screen Readers & Keyboard

- All components: keyboard navigable, labeled, correct roles/ARIA
- Inputs: visible label required; placeholder is not a label
- Modals: focus trap, return focus on close, one modal at a time
- Alerts: dismissible alerts need accessible close control

## Reduced Motion

Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`:

- Non-essential animation → `motion.duration.instant`
- Opacity fade only, max **100ms** for modal/alert enter
- No parallax, scale, or slide transforms
- No autoplay decorative motion; spinners may rotate but must not pulse or bounce
